  "text": "Our method begins with a one-mode projection of bipartite network B onto tag nodes, which produces G, a unipartite network of tags (see Fig. 1c ). From G, we filter out the insignificant connections between tag nodes (condition (i)) by using z-score of observed co-occurrence N (u, v) in B from the probability distribution of expected co-occurrences [CITATION_1] . Assuming the bipartite configuration model where degrees are preserved, the probability distribution of expected co-occurrence follows a hypergeometric distribution, yielding",
